Value:

({                                                                  \
        int32_t retval = 0, dir = 0;                                    \
        if (rd_wr & VQEC_DEV_IPC_IOCTL_WRITE) {                         \
            dir |= _IOC_WRITE;                                          \
        }                                                               \
        if (rd_wr & VQEC_DEV_IPC_IOCTL_READ) {                          \
            dir |= _IOC_READ;                                           \
        }                                                               \
        retval =                                                        \
            ioctl(s_vqec_dp_kmod_devid,                                 \
                  _IOC(dir, VQEC_DEV_IPC_IOCTL_TYPE,                    \
                       req->__rpc_fcn_num, req_size), NULL);            \
        retval;                                                         \
    })
--------------------------------------------------------------------------- Invoke a IPC system call [most parameters are unused for now].

Parameters:
[in] req [char*] Pointer to the request object (in shared memory).
[in] req_size [int] Request object size in bytes.
[out] rsp [char *] Pointer to the response object (in shared memory).
[out] rsp_size [int *] Response object size (pointer) in bytes.
[in] rd_wr [int] Bitmask specifying if the request is read-only, write-only or both read-write. The macro returns the return-value of the ioctl system call. ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
